13/01/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Dragan Marsicanin, deputy head of Vojislav Kostunica's Democratic Party of Serbia, said Monday (12 January) that a minority government for one year might be Serbia's best option.
He added that the main task of the new government would be to adopt a new constitution.
Party leaders will decide how to proceed Wednesday based on meetings with the G17 Plus party, the Democratic Party, and the Serbian Renewal Movement - New Serbia coalition.
In other news Monday, Montenegrin authorities denied the existence of an ethnic Albanian extremist group in the republic.
Officials were responding to reports that the interior ministry was looking into the existence of a group that had threatened to strike key sites.
(Beta, BBC - 12/01/04)
